title: US airman who helped thwart French train attack is stabbed
text: > Top News US airman who helped thwart French train attack is stabbed FILE - In this Sept. 17, 2015 file photo, Defense Secretary Ash Carter, left, raises the injured left arm of Airman 1st Class Spencer Stone, before Stone received the Airman's Medal and Purple Heart medal, during a ceremony at the Pentagon in Washington. An Air Force spokesman says Stone, who helped subdue an attacker on a Paris-bound train in August, is in stable condition after being stabbed in California. (AP Photo/Pablo Martinez Monsivais, File)
